<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="353" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1430,1923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1826,1851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has a restricted distribution in Honshu and Shikoku. This species is a well known pest of shiitake mushrooms in Honshu and Shikoku. The female genitalia of the Taiwanese specimen illustrated by Robinson (
<number box="[274,334,1898,1923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="353" value="1986.0">1986</number>
; Figs. 
<number box="[407,450,1899,1923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="353" value="141.0">141</number>
) agree with those of 
<taxonomicName box="[686,848,1899,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Morophagoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="353" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[686,848,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="353">M. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
